{"id":"spouse","term":"Spouse","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 4:8\">Cant. 4:8-12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 4:13\">Hos. 4:13</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 4:14\">14</a>) may denote either husband or wife, but in the Scriptures it denotes only the latter.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Song of Solomon 4:8","Hosea 4:13","Hosea 4:14"]}